    <!-- PROJECT DETAILS -->
    <div class="project-details">

        <h2>Project Overview</h2>
        <p>
            Brew Haven is a dynamic ASP.NET MVC coffee shop web application that allows users to
            manage orders, view analytics, and access nutrition information through an external API.
            The system integrates a database for persistent data and provides a modern, user-friendly interface.
        </p>

        <h2>Technical Details</h2>

        <h3>API Endpoint Used</h3>
        <p>
            API Ninjas Nutrition API:
            <br />
            <code>https://api.api-ninjas.com/v1/nutrition?query=</code>
        </p>

        <h3>Data Model (ERD)</h3>
        <p>
            The system includes entities such as Customers, Orders, and Menu Items.
            Relationships between these entities are defined through an Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD),
            which supports database-driven operations and structured data management.
        </p>

        <img src="~/images/erd.png" alt="ERD Diagram" class="erd-img" />

        <h3>CRUD Functionality</h3>
        <p>
            The application fully implements Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations.
            Users can create new orders, view order lists, update order details,
            and delete records from the system.
        </p>

        <h3>Technical Challenges & Solutions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Integrated an external nutrition API and handled inconsistent JSON responses.</li>
            <li>Resolved GitHub merge conflicts during team collaboration.</li>
            <li>Connected the application to an external database for persistent storage.</li>
            <li>Transformed static HTML into a dynamic MVC architecture using Razor views.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>GitHub Repository</h2>
        <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/Xeniyaky/Coffee-Shop-Group-10/blob/main/README.md" target="_blank">
                View Full Technical Documentation on GitHub
            </a>
        </p>

    </div>
